<font color="#FF0000">NURSES, CORPMAN &amp; MEDICS</font><br>
<tt>Sun May 18 14:15:48 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
To the nurses, Corpman and Medics.  I never met a single one who didn't gain and deserve my instant respect!  My thoughts often go back to a man I knew only as 'Mac', our Corpman at LZ Baldy.  For some inexplicable reason,New Years Eve, 1969 is burned into my memory.  He and I sat there discussing, not the war, but the politics behind the war.  Where ever you are 'Mac', may life still be a smile.<br><br>
To Jim Davey:  We to, played, (and caught hell for playing with), syringes on the USS Repose.  Powerful little suckers weren't they?
<p><code>--   (Zingara) </code><p>


